<p>Looking at the <a href="http://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation/comprehension" target="_blank">official UDL guidelines for providing options for comprehension</a>, everything appears to suggest direct instruction. I know that thatâ€™s not always en vogue with the science curriculum crowd, and I strongly suspect that this is is because most of these folksâ€™ most recent experience with direct instruction was a university professor droning at a blackboard. But direct instruction does not preclude students getting a lab and getting their hands dirty. It doesnâ€™t preclude learning from experience! But it does mean we have to clearly and directly provide the scaffolding students need to make sense of that experiential learning.</p>

