<h2 id="for-perception-and-recruiting-interest">For perception and recruiting interest</h2>
<h3 id="lots-of-different-methods-of-information-transferboth-from-me-and-from-my-students">Lots of different methods of information transferâ€”both from me and from my students!</h3>
<p>Students with auditory impairments canâ€™t rely solely on a verbal lecture; students with visual impairments canâ€™t rely solely on slideshowsâ€”I need to be responsive and flexible in how I present information so that I can meet all my students needs! Plus, presenting information in the same way every day may create a reliable routine, but will also be very boring. Meanwhile, presenting the <em>same</em> information in <em>multiple</em> ways gives everyone a chance to engage with the material, and gives more opportunity for students to consider an idea from multiple perspectives.</p>

